{"type":"message","id":"55a99c49","parentId":"4231cd9c","timestamp":"2026-03-24T18:20:28.203Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_o8id9vomzfv7_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 141816\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: state/goals.md (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine the most impactful single action.\r\n\r\nCurrent situation:\r\n- Phase 0 and Phase 1 (architecture analysis) are complete\r\n- CFI Compression experiment was completed successfully\r\n- Key finding: Need hybrid CFI×Freq scoring, not binary thresholds\r\n- Pending: Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment (Strategy C)\r\n\r\nThe most logical next action is to implement and run the Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment (Strategy C) that was identified as the next step from the CFI compression synthesis.\r\n\r\nThis involves:\r\n1. Creating or modifying code to implement the scoring formula: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n2. Running it on the 200 pulses\r\n3. Comparing against the previous results\r\n\r\nLet me look at what files exist that I could use as a foundation. The experiment was run on 200 pulses (80/20 split). The CFI compression synthesis doc mentions the scoring approach.\r\n\r\nI should create the experiment script for Strategy C (hybrid scoring) and run it. But wait - I need to be careful about what I can actually do. I'm a stateless agent, so I need to make concrete file edits.\r\n\r\nLooking at the pending actions:\r\n- [ ] Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment (Strategy C)\r\n\r\nThe most direct way to advance this is to implement the scoring formula and test it. I need to look at how the previous experiment was structured.\r\n\r\nFrom the synthesis doc reference, the key formula is:\r\nscore(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n\r\nThis scores tokens where:\r\n- CFI ≥ 0.5 (token is predictable)\r\n- freq ≥ 3 (token has appeared multiple times)\r\n- freq < 120 (token is not constant-format)\r\n\r\nThe hybrid approach should:\r\n1. Calculate this score for each token\r\n2. Use it to filter meaningful tokens vs metaprogramming artifacts\r\n\r\n\r\n3. Validate the method by comparing performance across different token selection strategies\r\n\r\nI'll develop a script that implements the new scoring mechanism, focusing on precise token classification and performance evaluation. The goal is to create a more nuanced approach to token selection that balances predictability and frequency.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe CFI compression synthesis identified Strategy C (hybrid CFI×Freq scoring) as the next critical experiment, with formula: `score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)`. This needs to be implemented and tested against the 80/20 pulse split used in prior experiments.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the Strategy C hybrid scoring experiment script, implementing the three-dimensional filter (CFI ≥ 0.5 AND freq ∈ [3, 120)) using the composite scoring formula. This directly advances the pending compression experiment.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n`\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # Strategy C: Hybrid CFI×Freq Scoring Experiment\r\n# Formula: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n# Filter: CFI >= 0.5 AND freq ∈ [3, 120)\r\n\r\n$pulseDir = \"pulse_data\"\r\n$pulses = Get-ChildItem $pulseDir -Filter \"pulse_*.md\" | Sort-Object Name\r\n$total = $pulses.Count\r\n$trainSize = [math]::Floor($total * 0.8)\r\n$trainPulses = $pulses[0..($trainSize-1)]\r\n$testPulses = $pulses[$trainSize..($total-1)]\r\n\r\n# Phase 1: Build vocabulary from training set\r\n$vocab = @{}\r\nforeach ($p in $trainPulses) {\r\n    $content = Get-Content $p.FullName -Raw\r\n    $tokens = [regex]::Matches($content, '\\S+') | ForEach-Object { $_.Value }\r\n    foreach ($t in $tokens) {\r\n        if ($vocab.ContainsKey($t)) { $vocab[$t]++ } else { $vocab[$t] = 1 }\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Phase 2: Calculate CFI for each token\r\n$cfiScores = @{}\r\n$totalTrain = $trainPulses.Count\r\n$vocabCount = $vocab.Count\r\n$progress = 0\r\n\r\nforeach ($token in $vocab.Keys) {\r\n    $freq = $vocab[$token]\r\n    $countInFirst = 0\r\n    \r\n    $firstHalf = $trainPulses[0..[math]::Floor($totalTrain/2)-1]\r\n    foreach ($p in $firstHalf) {\r\n        $content = Get-Content $p.FullName -Raw\r\n        if ($content -match [regex]::Escape($token)) { $countInFirst++ }\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    $p_observed = $freq / $totalTrain\r\n    $p_baseline = 1.0 / $vocabCount\r\n    $cfi = $p_observed / $p_baseline\r\n    \r\n    # Apply three-dimensional filter\r\n    $score = 0\r\n    if ($cfi -ge 0.5 -and $freq -ge 3 -and $freq -lt 120) {\r\n        $score = $cfi * [Math]::Min(1, $freq / 120)\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    $cfiScores[$token] = @{\r\n        CFI = $cfi\r\n        Freq = $freq\r\n        Score = $score\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    $progress++\r\n    if ($progress % 100 -eq 0) { Write-Host \"Processed $progress / $vocabCount tokens\" }\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Phase 3: Calculate precision on test set\r\n$highScoreTokens = ($cfiScores.GetEnumerator() | Where-Object { $_.Value.Score -gt 0 } | Sort-Object\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 14:18:37\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774376428200}}
